items.name: SMOL, a mod manager
items.summary: ## Beta 15
items.description:
## Beta 15

To update, launch SMOL and follow the update prompt.
In case of "Access is denied" error (Windows Defender false positive), see "Auto-Update broken?" video above.

New: **Tip Deleter**
- See which mods tips came from...
- And remove them!
- Deleted tips are remembered even when you update a mod  

Notes: Tips are removed from all versions of a mod that you have. Removing a tip rewrites the tip file after creating a backup (so any comments from the author are removed). There is no "undo", but since it creates a backup in the tips folder, you can just swap back.

**Also**
- There is now **experimental Linux and MacOS** support, but you have to build it yourself, sorry 🙂 Thank you to <@615999112692891658> for adding the Linux support!
- Fixed download notifications (I hope, they work for me anyway) and added notifs for download errors.
- Disabled mods are no longer enabled when you use the one-click updater.
- Mod profiles are now sorted by last updated.

items.name: Thog's Domain (THG)
items.summary: Update, Version 4: More additions, and more minor tweaks.
items.description:
Update, Version 4: More additions, and more minor tweaks.

CHANGES:

Added "Delicate Machinery" to Bulkhead and Phasedigm, to represent their respective complex mechanical natures.

Increased supply usage, and slightly reduced peak operation time of Bulkhead to represent it's delicate nature

Added Oculus, a destroyer-sized drone with a 360 degree large weapon mount and minor missile armament, utilizing fast missile racks to get the most out of it's two small missile slots.

Added Oracle, a phase variation on the Oculus which trades it's large ballistic mounting for a medium hybrid, and it's fast missile racks for a degraded phase skimmer.

Added Jury, an assault-oriented destroyer carrier with a large weapon mount and a single fighter bay, with the ability to release reserve fighters in a pinch.

Added Billiard, ~~a mudskipper MKII that doesn't suck balls~~ a drone artillery platform capable of mounting either a large missile or ballistic weapon to devastating effect, thanks to it's Lidar array system and comparitive practicality compared to other alternatives in a similar role.

Added Laggard Automortar, a small ballistic ammunition-reliant variation of the light mortar with a higher-than-standard rate of fire, though with a marginally reduced range and even less accuracy.

Added Chamberlain Mining Drone, a highly utilitous autonomous bomber with a built-in mining laser and capacity to carry and fire a single hammerhead torpedo. Nimbler than the common Perdition bomber and more well defended, though fragile and slow to replace by comparison, and with one less craft to a wing.

Should be save compatible, direct DL link above has been updated.
